                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.77 Manchuria/155: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Krentz</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-23T15:00:00+09:00"
                            >July 23, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 25—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. Railway announces effective tomorrow sale of round trip, season, excursion,
                    limited express (Asia), sleeping car and platform tickets is suspended “for the
                    time being.” Stopovers, changes of route or destination, changes of class, and
                    refunds for unused tickets will not be permitted. Luggage and express shipments
                    are also drastically curtailed. Hand luggage will be limited to two pieces per
                    passenger not exceeding one cubic meter and checked luggage to two pieces not
                    exceeding 100 kilograms. We have been orally informed today that no tickets will
                    be granted to foreigners destined to Rashin, <pb facs="0428" n="418"
                        xml:id="pg_418"/> Seishin, Fusan or Dairen whether or not they are destined
                    to Japan and that foreigners may leave for North China only with special
                    permission of the authorities. Travel to Fusan is also restricted for
                    Japanese.</p>
                <p>Sent to Peiping. Repeated to Tokyo, Harbin, Dairen.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Krentz</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
